## Go further

### A. Check array functions

PostgreSQL has specialized array operators and functions for arrays. ([PostgreSQL][3])

```sql
SELECT array_length(ARRAY['a', 'b', 'c'], 1) AS item_count;
```

### B. Build JSON arrays from relational data

PostgreSQL documents generating JSON objects and arrays from relational data as part of its SQL/JSON support. ([PostgreSQL][5])

```sql
SELECT jsonb_build_array('Python', 'SQL', 'Julia') AS languages;
```

### C. Table expressions as virtual tables

PostgreSQL describes table expressions as producing a virtual table passed through the query pipeline. ([PostgreSQL][2])

```sql
SELECT title
FROM books
WHERE pages > 250;
```


